{"article_id":"7Ys9K74nkhlUNvf9","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"\" Chicago prosecutors on Tuesday dropped charges","depth":8},{"id":1,"text":"accusing ' Empire ' actor Jussie Smollett of staging a phony hate crime ...","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"The Cook County State ' s Attorney ' s office said","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"it viewed the outcome as appropriate...","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"First Assistant State ' s Attorney Joseph Magats told the Chicago Sun-Times","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"that the decision","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"to drop the case","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"did not mean Smollett is innocent of the charges ,","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"or that he was a victim. \"","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"Reuters","depth":5},{"id":10,"text":"On Wednesday , the Chicago Police Department released its file on the case .","depth":4},{"id":11,"text":"ABC 7 Chicago","depth":3},{"id":12,"text":"Many on both sides are highly critical of the prosecutor :","depth":4},{"id":13,"text":"\" It ' s an indefensible decision , a deal","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"hashed out in secret ,","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"with","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"- this is outrageous -","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"Smollett not even required to take ownership of his apparent hoax .","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"Not even required to apologize","depth":12},{"id":19,"text":"for allegedly exploiting hate crime laws .","depth":12},{"id":20,"text":"And not even required to reimburse Chicago taxpayers for the enormous cost of this investigation...","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"Unless there ' s yet one more big revelation in this case","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"that makes the prosecutors ' decision sensible ,","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"it will further erode citizens ' trust in law enforcement. \"","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"Editorial Board , Chicago Tribune","depth":6},{"id":25,"text":"\" Whatever Mr. Magats may pretend about this being no exoneration ,","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"Mr. Smollett and his attorneys are claiming exactly that .","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"Mr. Smollett asserted","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"as he left the courthouse","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"that he ' s been ' truthful and consistent ' from the start ,","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"and he ' s still claiming","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"he was attacked by two people","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"he was unable to identify .","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"Mayor Emanuel and Police Superintendent Johnson are right .","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"This deal stinks ,","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"and the city of Chicago deserves an apology . \"","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"Editorial Board , Wall Street Journal","depth":6},{"id":37,"text":"Other opinions below .","depth":4},{"id":38,"text":"From the Left","depth":6},{"id":39,"text":"Chicago mayor Rahm Emanuel held a press conference","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"in which he stated ,","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"`` This is an unbelievable... whitewash of justice ,","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"this is a person now","depth":13},{"id":43,"text":"who got off scot-free with no sense of accountability of the moral and ethical wrong of his actions , from top to bottom ,","depth":15},{"id":44,"text":"not only besmirching the name of the city ...","depth":15},{"id":45,"text":"but you have a person","depth":15},{"id":46,"text":"using hate crime laws","depth":18},{"id":47,"text":"that are on the books","depth":18},{"id":48,"text":"to protect people","depth":18},{"id":49,"text":"who are minorities from violence ,","depth":18},{"id":50,"text":"to turn around","depth":17},{"id":51,"text":"and use those laws","depth":18},{"id":52,"text":"to advance your career ?","depth":18},{"id":53,"text":"Is there no decency in this man ? ''","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"\" The explanation was as forced","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"as it was false .","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"First , Cook County presumably has not decided to confine prosecutions to violent crimes ,","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"or everything from blackmail to bank fraud to tax evasion would be effectively immunized...","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"\" This was not just any nonviolent offense .","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"Smollett sent a city into crisis","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"and caused the Chicago Police Department to direct huge resources into the search for racist , homophobic Trump supporters","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"terrorizing innocent citizens .","depth":12},{"id":62,"text":"Magats said","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"that the office did not want to use limited resources","depth":13},{"id":64,"text":"to go after nonviolent crime ,","depth":13},{"id":65,"text":"but it already spent those resources","depth":14},{"id":66,"text":"in uncovering the hoax","depth":15},{"id":67,"text":"and securing 16 charges .","depth":15},{"id":68,"text":"All","depth":14},{"id":69,"text":"that remained was what looked like a perfunctory trial . \"","depth":14},{"id":70,"text":"\" I started caring about the Smollett story","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"because of the reaction to the story ,","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"because we 've come to view the justice system as just another tool","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"to push political agendas","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"instead of the best way","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"to determine truth","depth":13},{"id":76,"text":"and ensure justice...","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"[ For example ] many liberals howled","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"when Paul Manafort was given ' only ' four years in prison","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"-- even though liberals have been fighting against mass incarceration and unduly long and harsh prison sentences... \"","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"Smollett should n't be top of mind ,","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"no matter whether he 's telling the truth","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"or really staged a phony attack","depth":13},{"id":83,"text":"to boost his chances","depth":14},{"id":84,"text":"of getting a raise .","depth":14},{"id":85,"text":"But he is .","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"That does n't mean he should be scapegoated for our inability","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"to focus on things far more important .","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"That 's our fault ,","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"not his . \"","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"Some argue","depth":7},{"id":91,"text":"that \" few enraged by Smollett ' s case seem to have considered what should be intuitive -","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"that Tuesday ' s decision was a perfectly reasonable response to a system","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"that locks up far too many people","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"while offering inadequate ways","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"to address the most serious crimes...","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"To the extent","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"that incarceration is ever appropriate in its current American manifestation ,","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"it should be used sparingly","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"to protect people from those","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"who would harm them .","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"Smollett clearly does not qualify . \"","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"Zak Cheney-Rice , New York Magazine","depth":6},{"id":103,"text":"From the Right","depth":2},{"id":104,"text":"\" Smollett is n't getting off","depth":6},{"id":105,"text":"because he is innocent .","depth":6},{"id":106,"text":"He is not innocent .","depth":6},{"id":107,"text":"He is something better than innocent .","depth":7},{"id":108,"text":"He is famous .","depth":7},{"id":109,"text":"The charges against him were dropped","depth":6},{"id":110,"text":"because someone in power called someone else in power","depth":7},{"id":111,"text":"and said ,","depth":8},{"id":112,"text":"' Let him go. '","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"None of this had anything to do with justice .","depth":6},{"id":114,"text":"It 's the opposite of justice . \"","depth":6},{"id":115,"text":"\" Hate crimes happen every day .","depth":7},{"id":116,"text":"Sometimes to gay black men .","depth":8},{"id":117,"text":"Sometimes to Muslims .","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"Sometimes to Jews .","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"Hoaxes make real victims seem less believable ,","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"and they also unnecessarily exacerbate racial and political tension...","depth":8},{"id":121,"text":"In a country","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"obsessed with the hierarchy of oppression ,","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"it ' s rare to see anyone call a black gay man privileged .","depth":9},{"id":124,"text":"But what else do you call a person","depth":9},{"id":125,"text":"who fakes a hate crime ,","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"gets off scot-free ,","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"and doesn ' t even offer so much as an apology ? \"","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"\" It ought to be blindingly obvious to Chicago prosecutors","depth":7},{"id":129,"text":"that","depth":8},{"id":130,"text":"if a hate-crime hoaxer is allowed to get away with it ,","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"this constitutes an engraved invitation to others","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"who might be inclined to paint themselves as victims","depth":12},{"id":133,"text":"and bask in the inevitable national-cynosure status","depth":12},{"id":134,"text":"while precious police resources get tied up in one of the most dangerous cities in America on the investigation of nonexistent crimes...","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"Some nominal fine and community service ,","depth":9},{"id":136,"text":"unaccompanied by a guilty plea ,","depth":9},{"id":137,"text":"fall far short of the degree of punishment","depth":8},{"id":138,"text":"that is necessary","depth":8},{"id":139,"text":"both to impress upon Smollett the gravity of what he has done","depth":9},{"id":140,"text":"and to deter future Smolletts from following his lead . \"","depth":9},{"id":141,"text":"Some argue","depth":8},{"id":142,"text":"that \" Smollett ' s celebrity and political connections may have been factors in the decisions","depth":10},{"id":143,"text":"made by Cook County prosecutors throughout the course of this case ,","depth":10},{"id":144,"text":"including State ' s Attorney Kim Foxx ' s decision","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"to recuse herself .","depth":10},{"id":146,"text":"But the unfortunate truth is that such leniency isn ' t rare in Chicago .","depth":8},{"id":147,"text":"Hardened criminals are constantly given sweet deals... \"","depth":8},{"id":148,"text":"Last December , Marcus Moore was released from prison","depth":9},{"id":149,"text":"after serving just five months of a sentence for an assault ,","depth":11},{"id":150,"text":"captured on camera ,","depth":11},{"id":151,"text":"that led to the death of Marques Gaines .","depth":10},{"id":152,"text":"Moore ,","depth":10},{"id":153,"text":"according to the Chicago Tribune ,","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"was ' a five-time felon with 33 arrests by Chicago police.","depth":9},{"id":155,"text":"' ...","depth":8},{"id":156,"text":"last summer , police charged two men with attempted murder","depth":10},{"id":157,"text":"after they live-streamed on Facebook the vicious beating of a 42-year-old man .","depth":10},{"id":158,"text":"The two were both on parole","depth":10},{"id":159,"text":"and had more than 20 prior arrests between them...","depth":10},{"id":160,"text":"Chicago violence is frequently committed by repeat offenders-many","depth":6},{"id":161,"text":"released with pending cases ,","depth":7},{"id":162,"text":"paroled","depth":9},{"id":163,"text":"after serving only a portion of their sentences ,","depth":9},{"id":164,"text":"or given probation","depth":9},{"id":165,"text":"despite troubling criminal histories . \"","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":331,"left":268,"right":330,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":268,"left":177,"right":267,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":177,"left":176,"right":11,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"